<br>
Please bring a rezzable cleric with you...a lot of clerics out there that do not have sprinklers are in groups and cannot afford the mana for a rez and such, especially if the group has no way to regen mana faster (bard, chanter, necro).  <br>
<br>
Lately wherever I go, I get tells for rezzes all the time, I don't mind doing them, even going out of my way to do them...but when I am in a group and I have to leave to do a rez, it is unfair for the group to have to wait x amount of minutes so someone can get rezzed.  <br>
<br>
I've gone so far as to go completely anon and still people see me in golden armor (well now purple) and ask me to run three zones over to rez someone.  And sometimes when we say no...we get verbal abuse.<br>
<br>
People need to understand that we clerics are here to play the game as well...we are not travelling HMOs.  If we cannot get to you for a rez...then I hate to say it, thats too bad.  I don't have a sprinkler.  A 90% exp rez at level 51 takes almost two blue bubs of mana.  In a group...thats a lot of mana without a bard or enchanter to help regen that.<br>
<br>
I'm a nice guy and have already gone out of my way to rez people, but when I get the impression that some people just expect clerics to drop everything to rez someone...that bothers me.  It's not our fault you didn't have a rezzable cleric in the group.  And don't flip on us either, because one day we will be able to rez you and we will remember who you are...and if you give us a hard time beforehand, we may choose not to.<br>
<br>
I'm not trying to sounds like a jerk on this post, I would gladly do a rez if the corpse was nearby my group or in the way of the path I travel...but to ask someone to go out of their way to rez and if that cleric says no to give them flak...thats just plain inconsiderate.<br>
<br>
